e (historian)|publisher=Naval Institute Press|year=1996}}</ref>\n|<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\n|[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|17px]]\n|May 20, 1801 <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|July 1, 1801 <ref name=\"NIHS\">{{cite book|isbn=978-1-55750-984-0|title=Naval Institute Historical Atlas of the U.S. Navy|last1=Symonds|first1=Craig L.|authorlink1=Craig L. Symonds|last2=Clipson|first2=William J.|author2-link=William J. Clipson|publisher=Naval Institute Press|year=2001}}</ref>\n|?\n|?\n|-\n|2\n|[[Commodore (United States)|COM]] [[Richard Valentine Morris|Richard Morris]] <ref name=\"AMFS\" /> <br /> (Second Squadron) <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\n|[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|17px]]\n|?\n|May 25, 1802 <ref name=\"Rodgers\">{{cite book|title=Commodore John Rodgers, Captain, Commodore, and Senior Officer of the American Navy, 1773\u20131838|last=Charles|first=Charles Oscar|authorlink=Charles Oscar Paullin|publisher=The Arthur H. Clark Company|year=1910}}</ref>\n|June 21, 1803 <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|September 11, 1803 <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|-\n|3\n|[[Commodore (United States)|COM]] [[John Rodgers (naval officer, War of 1812)|John Rodgers]] <ref name=\"Rodgers\" /> <br /> (Second Squadron) <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|[[File:Commodore John Rodgers.jpg|100px]]\n|[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|17px]]\n|June 21, 1803 <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|September 11, 1803 <ref name=\"Rodgers\" />\n|?\n|?\n|-\n|4\n|[[Commodore (United States)|COM]] [[Edward Preble]] <ref name=\"AMFS\" /> <br /> (Third Squadron) <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|[[File:Edward Preble.jpg|100px]]\n|[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|17px]]\n|May 19, 1803 <ref name=\"AMFS\" />\n|September, 1803 <ref name=\"NIHS\" />\n|1804 <ref name=\"AMFS\" />\n|?\n|-\n|5\n|[[Commodore (United States)|COM]] [[Samuel Barron (1765-1810)|Samuel Barron]] <ref name=\"Preble\" /> <br /> (Fourth Squadron) <ref name=\"Preble\" />\n|<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\n|[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|17px]]\n|April, 1804 <ref name=\"Rodgers\" />\